<title>FRANCE: Socialist opposition says French budget &quot;unjust&quot;.</title>
<headline>Socialist opposition says French budget &quot;unjust&quot;.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1996-09-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>The French opposition Socialist Party described the 1997 budget approved by the cabinet on Wednesday as inappropriate and unjust.</p>
<p>&quot;It is both inappropriate, because what we need today is a budget which fires up the economy, and unjust because we needed a budget which redistributed income through taxation,&quot; Socialist spokesman Francois Hollande told reporters.</p>
<p>-- Paris Newsroom +33 1 4221 5452</p>
